@startuml
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-SKILL)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-STORE)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-RENDER)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-PROFILE-DOC)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
'
' Objective-side ownership boundaries for /mdd-deploy. Canonical source
' of truth for the skill body is crates/mdd-core/src/templates.rs; mdd
' init materializes it into .claude/.codex SKILL.md. The deploy tree and
' the cross-repo Bicep are run-time outputs of the skill, not gated.
'
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-SKILL, "The /mdd-deploy utility skill: templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL plus its WORKFLOW_SKILLS entry and the .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md mirrors. Produces a deployment diagram + runbook + generated IaC and never executes a deploy command. A sibling of /mdd-render, outside the parity gate.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-STORE, ".mdd/deploy/<target>/ on disk: diagram.puml + runbook.md, created on first /mdd-deploy run. Naturally outside /mdd-validate and /mdd-review scope (same pattern as the non-gated .mdd/map/ tree).")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET, "The deployment target repo ../atlas-ate-server, read READ-ONLY for topology and security invariants. The generated infra/main.bicep (+ modules) is written there at skill-run time; cross-repo output is fine because the skill is non-gated guidance.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-RENDER, "/mdd-render extended (templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL step) to also rasterize .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive and non-gating.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-PROFILE-DOC, ".mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md, materialized from templates::deploy_profile_doc (MDD_DEPLOY_PROFILE_DOC): conventions for the Azure Container Apps deployment diagram and the invariant checklist, analogous to security-profile.md.")
title /mdd-deploy ownership (objective)

actor "Operator" as Op

component "/mdd-deploy\n(utility skill)" as Skill
component "/mdd-render\n(extended)" as Render

folder ".mdd/deploy/azure-container-apps/\ndiagram.puml, runbook.md" as Store
folder "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/main.bicep (+ modules)" as Target
folder ".mdd/rendered/deploy/\n**/*.svg" as Rendered
folder ".mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md" as ProfileDoc

package "canonical source of truth" {
  component "crates/mdd-core/src/templates.rs\nMDD_DEPLOY_SKILL + WORKFLOW_SKILLS\n+ MDD_DEPLOY_PROFILE_DOC" as Templates
}

package "existing gated MDD pipeline\n(unaffected)" {
  component "/mdd-cycle / /mdd-validate /\n/mdd-review (parity gate)" as Gate
}

Op --> Skill : /mdd-deploy <description>
Templates ..> Skill : materialized by `mdd init`
Templates ..> ProfileDoc : materialized by `mdd init`
Skill --> Store : write diagram.puml + runbook.md
Skill --> Target : generate infra/main.bicep (+ modules)
Skill ..> ProfileDoc : follows conventions
Op --> Render : /mdd-render
Render --> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render --> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg
Gate ..> Store : NEVER reads (outside the gate)

note bottom of Skill
  Guidance only. Never runs az / docker / brew.
  Realizes USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Gate
  /mdd-deploy is decoupled: no objective<->current
  parity, no @sec parity. A UML deployment diagram
  has no code-derived counterpart, so it could
  never reach parity — by design it is not routed
  into the gate.
end note
@enduml
